  "body": "R.-Z. Li, B.-T. Wang, J. Mao, X.-L. Zhang, J.-J. Zhang, and J.-M. Bai (YNAO) report:\n\nWe followed the GCN circular on the discovery of an optical transient as a new blazar candidate in the Messier 31 field (Gianluca et al. GCN 34819). We observed the transient with the 2.4-meter optical telescope at Gao-Mei-Gu (GMG) station of Yunnan Observatories. The preliminary results are shown as\n----------------------------------------------------\nUT\t\t\t\tfilter\tmag\n----------------------------------------------------\n2023-10-17T14:16:13.243\t\tB\t20.14 ± 0.12\n2023-10-17T14:19:54.225\t\tV\t17.80 ± 0.09\n2023-10-17T14:23:29.236\t\tR\t18.44 ± 0.06\n2023-10-18T16:12:25.346\t\tB\t20.68 ± 0.15\n2023-10-18T16:16:00.356\t\tV\t18.13 ± 0.10\n2023-10-18T16:19:35.370\t\tR\t18.89 ± 0.07\n2023-10-19T15:37:25.492\t\tB\t20.23 ± 0.10\n2023-10-19T15:41:07.493\t\tV\t17.62 ± 0.06\n2023-10-19T15:45:03.473\t\tR\t18.38 ± 0.04\n2023-10-20T15:17:30.676\t\tB\t20.24 ± 0.13\n2023-10-20T15:21:09.646\t\tV\t17.71 ± 0.08\n2023-10-20T15:24:49.624\t\tR\t18.41 ± 0.05\n2023-10-21T15:12:50.704\t\tB\t19.83 ± 0.15\n2023-10-21T15:16:30.683\t\tV\t17.77 ± 0.09\n2023-10-21T15:20:08.724\t\tR\t18.26 ± 0.06\n2023-10-22T14:27:55.829\t\tB\t20.54 ± 0.16\n2023-10-22T14:31:36.818\t\tV\t17.87 ± 0.10\n2023-10-22T14:35:17.806\t\tR\t18.90 ± 0.06\n----------------------------------------------------\nThe further identification is ongoing.\n"
